				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The problem stems from simply making a class being categorized into a main function (tanking) and then not being able to do it as well as another class. 
<br />

<br />
EQ2 (the offical posts from their spokesperson on Sony's board) is supposed to focus on this "not" being the case. ie. Fix it.
<br />

<br />
Druids, Shaman and Clerics are all healers. They should all be able to sustain healing the same amount, the 2nd tier of abilities are what should be different. Clerics with raw HP buffs and rez. Shaman with stat buffs and DoTs. Druids with porting and nuking. But as they are all part of the healing master class in EQ2 they intend to balance them so they are EQUAL HEALERS. 
<br />

<br />
That is a very good idea. 
<br />

<br />
That should be done in EQ1.
<br />

<br />
Warriors, Pallys and SK's are all flat out tanks. They should all be able to survive as long on the same mob with the same gear and same buffs. How Sony should accomplish this is up to them. For example, Warrior with Defensive. Pallys with stuns that land on "anything", mitigating damage for as long as thier mana holds out, SKs with much bigger lifetaps, etc. Just saying, I dont understand why posts seem to indicate they "get it" in EQ2, but they refuse to "correct it" in EQ1.  Mistake :(</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
